Mar-12-2012: Physical Salvation as the true Purpose of Religion

==Plea
We, the people, must be the change we seek.
We will replace corporation and government.

We will buy land and water-rights and tools and plants
and animals needed for reproduction of our daily bread.

But we must structure ourselves differently from within
lest we grow into yet another head of that deadly beast.


==Summary
Production requires both material and immaterial Sources.

===Definitions
Material Sources (MS) include the surface-area, water,
living organisms, tools, energy needed to produce our
food, medicine, soap, cloth, building materials, etc.

Immaterial Sources (IS) are things such as such as software
or hardware design or genetics or 3D models and other media.

Products are the goods and services we need.


===The GNU Pattern
The GNU GPL is a sort of trade-agreement between the owners
of IS which protects Product Users by requiring those users
gain at-cost access to the IS of that production.

This may seem useless, since most Users do not know how to
use the IS.  In other words, most Users are not Developers
of that exact Product, and so what would they do with the
Source-Code or DNA or design documents?

Of course some Users will study the IS and hopefully learn
how to make their own Products.

But the more significant impact of Users gaining at-cost
access to Sources is how it reduces the barriers to entry.

Now the User can hire any Worker, because the Sources are
almost all that is needed for production to begin.



